Subject: [PATCH AP-12] vmmon: add MODULE_IMPORT_NS for symbol namespace (kernel >= 5.15)

Linux 5.15 introduced symbol namespaces for kernel-exported symbols. When a
kernel is built with CONFIG_MODULE_ALLOW_MISSING_NAMESPACE_IMPORTS=n (the
stricter setting), modules that use symbols from a namespace must declare
MODULE_IMPORT_NS() or they will fail to load with a taint or outright refusal.

This is distribution-specific: most distros do not enforce strict namespace
imports for external modules, but some (especially those with hardened
configurations) do.

The fix adds MODULE_IMPORT_NS("VMWCORE") before the existing MODULE_LICENSE()
line in vmmon's driver.c. The script applies this patch only when the kernel
headers indicate that symbol namespaces are in use (heuristic: EXPORT_SYMBOL_NS
present in kernel include tree).

Applied by: _autopatch_module_import_ns() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  kernel >= 5.15 AND kernel uses symbol namespaces

---
 vmmon-only/linux/driver.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/vmmon-only/linux/driver.c b/vmmon-only/linux/driver.c
--- a/vmmon-only/linux/driver.c
+++ b/vmmon-only/linux/driver.c
@@ -1422,6 +1422,7 @@ MODULE_AUTHOR("VMware, Inc.");
 MODULE_DESCRIPTION("VMware Virtual Machine Monitor.");
+MODULE_IMPORT_NS("VMWCORE");
 MODULE_LICENSE("GPL v2");
